    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What drives property values in Wishart?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Wishart property values are driven by its larger-than-average residential blocks, strong school catchments, quiet streets, and its position in the southern Brisbane corridor that gives families practical access to Garden City shopping, the South East Freeway, and the amenity of the Mount Gravatt precinct. The suburb attracts families who are actively trading space for the inner-suburb density they have left behind, and those buyers place clear value on the generous outdoor space and established character that Wishart consistently delivers. Homes on well-maintained internal streets within the best catchments attract steady competition from committed family buyers." }
    },
