    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the lifestyle like in Wishart?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Wishart offers an established, family-focused lifestyle approximately twelve kilometres south of the Brisbane CBD. The suburb is defined by its quiet residential streets, larger family homes on good-sized blocks, and practical proximity to Garden City and the Mount Gravatt commercial precinct. It is a suburb that suits families who want outdoor space, established character, and reliable access to school catchments and everyday retail without the density of the inner suburbs. The predominance of long-term owner-occupiers gives Wishart a settled residential character that makes it a genuine family destination rather than a transitional address." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is Wishart a good suburb to buy in right now?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Wishart offers compelling value for families comparing the southern Brisbane corridor. The suburb delivers larger blocks, established character, school catchments, and proximity to Garden City and the South East Freeway at a price point that reflects its position as a family destination rather than a prestige address. Consistent demand from families making a deliberate decision to move south for space and catchments has supported the market, and the suburb's settled owner-occupier base makes it a sound long-term family ownership proposition." }
    }
  ]
})}</script>


