    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      The school catchments in Wishart and the surrounding area are a primary draw for families comparing the southern corridor. Buyers who have been researching school options across this part of Brisbane have typically identified the catchments available here as a key reason to make the move south, and when a family has committed to a catchment, their motivation at your open home is different in quality from that of a casual browser. They have resolved the most important question in their decision, and what remains is finding the right property at the right price. That committed buyer intent is a meaningful advantage for sellers who present their home well.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Wishart's housing stock is dominated by established family homes, many of which sit on blocks that are larger than what is typically available at comparable price points closer to the CBD. That additional outdoor space, along with the quiet street character and the proximity to Garden City and the South East Freeway, is the combination that keeps families in Wishart for the long term once they have made the move. Sellers who understand what drove their own decision to buy here are well-placed to communicate the same value to the next buyer.
    </p>
