        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Wishart property values are driven by its larger residential blocks, strong school catchments, quiet streets and easy access to Garden City and the South East Freeway. The suburb attracts families who are prioritising space, and that consistent family demand from buyers who have compared the southern corridor and settled on Wishart supports steady market performance. Homes on well-maintained internal streets within the best catchments attract the most competitive buyer interest.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          How long does it take to sell a home in Wishart?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Well-priced Wishart homes typically sell within 25 to 40 days. Family buyers in the southern corridor tend to be well-researched and motivated once they have identified the right suburb and catchment, and they act decisively when a property at the right price appears. Autumn and spring bring the strongest open home activity, but the southern corridor produces consistent family buyer demand throughout the year.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What is the lifestyle like in Wishart?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Wishart offers a quiet, established family lifestyle approximately twelve kilometres from the Brisbane CBD. The suburb is defined by larger residential blocks, well-maintained homes, and easy access to Garden City shopping and the South East Freeway. School catchments are a primary driver for the family buyers who are most prevalent in the area. It is a suburb defined by long-term ownership and the community that comes with a settled, family-oriented residential base.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          Is Wishart a good suburb to buy in right now?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Wishart offers solid value for families comparing the southern Brisbane corridor. The suburb delivers larger blocks, school catchments and quiet streets at a price point that reflects its position as a family destination rather than a prestige address. Consistent demand from families making a deliberate move south for space and school access has supported the market, and the suburb's established character and low turnover make it a compelling long-term owner-occupier proposition.</p>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

